  "chapter": {
    "number": 64,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Prayer for Godâ€™s Power"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If only You would rend the heavens and come down,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that mountains would quake at Your presence,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "as fire kindles the brushwood",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and causes the water to boil,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to make Your name known to Your enemies,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that the nations will tremble at Your presence!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When You did awesome works that we did not expect,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You came down, and the mountains trembled at Your presence.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "From ancient times no one has heard,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no ear has perceived,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "no eye has seen any God besides You,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who acts on behalf of those who wait for Him.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2739
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You welcome those who gladly do right,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who remember Your ways.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Surely You were angry, for we sinned.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "How can we be saved if we remain in our sins?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Each of us has become like something unclean,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all our righteous acts are like filthy rags;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2740
          },
          {
            "text": "we all wither like a leaf,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and our iniquities carry us away like the wind.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "No one calls on Your name",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or strives to take hold of You.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For You have hidden Your face from us",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and delivered us into the hand",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2741
          },
          {
            "text": "of our iniquity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But now, O LORD, You are our Father;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "we are the clay, and You are the potter;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "we are all the work of Your hand.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not be angry, O LORD, beyond measure;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not remember our iniquity forever.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Oh, look upon us, we pray;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "we are all Your people!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your holy cities have become a wilderness.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Zion has become a wasteland and Jerusalem a desolation.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Our holy and beautiful temple,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "where our fathers praised You,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "has been burned with fire,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all that was dear to us lies in ruins.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "After all this, O LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will You restrain Yourself?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Will You keep silent",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and afflict us beyond measure?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
